      "side": 1,
      "message": "It turns out that the settings values are cached on the initial compile, and baked in later, when optimize() is called. The obvious fix is to just re-compile the shader from scratch when building for GPU. I figured that if we\u0027re doing all the other steps (specialization, SkSL generation, re-parsing, emitting GLSL, calling the driver), that doing the first parse isn\u0027t that much more overhead right now. (Eventually, we probably want to reconsider this all...)\n\nHowever, the specialized program has pointers into data structures in the original program, so I had to move all this into one function to manage object lifetime properly. The outputs of this function are completely encapsulated, though, and don\u0027t depend on any of the temporary programs created here.",
