      "message": "The next big piece (that I started, but decided to save for a follow-up CL) is to stop storing SkSL::Type objects (in fInAndUniformVars), and instead pre-parse those into a simpler struct for the public API (including offset into data blob, name, CPU type, uniform type). That would eliminate another long-lived pointer into a compiler-owned structure, and make it easier for clients to ask about the layout of uniforms they need to supply.\n\nAs part of that, I\u0027m *strongly* recommending that we remove \u0027layout(ctype)\u0027 from runtime SkSL. It really doesn\u0027t make any sense (we don\u0027t generate code, so it only affects how we interpret the input blob), and complicates the variable handling code quite a bit (we need to do the same alterations to data in setData, and we need to account for the different-from-expected size when walking the inputs). It would require this one spot to actually expand the color array to floats before passing it to the FP.",
      "revId": "b6c1c8f5b844bf83a3c4fcec0b1bee907bb7b732",
